### Potential Race Condition and Redundant Initialization

The current implementation of `ensureDatabase` uses polling and a timeout to wait for the database to initialize. If multiple concurrent calls to `ensureDatabase` are made (e.g., from parallel requests), each will start its own polling and timeout logic, which can lead to redundant polling, unnecessary resource usage, and possible race conditions when setting `this.db`.

**Recommendation:**
- Use a shared promise to track the initialization state, so that concurrent calls to `ensureDatabase` await the same promise and do not start redundant polling/timers.
- Example approach:
  ```ts
  private dbInitPromise: Promise<void> | null = null;
  private async ensureDatabase(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.db) return;
    if (!this.dbInitPromise) {
      this.dbInitPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        // ...existing polling logic...
      });
    }
    await this.dbInitPromise;
  }
  ```
- This pattern prevents multiple concurrent initializations and simplifies timer management.

